info:
# Splitters (FIT/Normal)
by: Firebee

# Description
These are two splitter types! Both for different uses
> FIT splitters take out the first item type found in the box and load a new box with those items. When that item type runs out both boxes are broke 
> Normal splitters unload the full box separating nonstackable items out before the box loader. They break the loader box when a new item type is detected and the unloader box is only broken once empty

# Credits
- Helped explain FIT logic: Prepusio

# Extra
Both local and global clock versions of each type can be found in the WDLs
